BFN 

  [Text] Pyongyang, April 14 (KCNA) -- The Central Committee 
of the Workers' Party of Korea [WPK] Wednesday gave a party for 
the visiting delegation of the Workers' Party of Ireland. 
  Secretary of the C.C. [Central Committee], the WPK Hwang 
Chang-yop, addressing the party, said that the Workers' Party of 
Ireland [WPI], under the slogan "future is socialism", is now 
positively striving for the neutrality and non-alignment of 
Ireland against the war policy and arms race of the 
imperialists, strengthening the party and unity with the masses. 
  He warmly congratulated the WPI on growing stronger and 
developing into a massive party with each passing day and 
expressed positive support and solidarity to their noble 
struggle for independence and socialism against imperialism. 
  General Secretary of the WPI Pat Quearney in his speech 
expressed thanks for the hospitality accorded to his delegation 
and said they would learn much from the Korean people. 
  Assuring that he will introduce the Korean people's struggle 
to the Irish people and conduct a struggle against the U.S. 
policy towards Korea, he hoped that all questions facing the 
Korean people would be settled in a peaceful way. 

